I am an admin member of {{theteam}}. I try to access the members of {{thegroup}} (of which I&#x27;m a member) using

{code}
https://api.bitbucket.org/1.0/groups/theteam/thegroup/members
{code}

but this returns {{Forbidden}}. It seems like I can query some team information as a member, but not all. Shouldn&#x27;t an admin member of the team be able to query everything?

There is an issue where wikis containing unrecognized lexer specifications with the notation

{{{\\
#!language\\
}}}

aren&#x27;t rendered at all. This can be worked around by providing a language from http://pygments.org/docs/lexers/#lexers-for-agile-languages in the short names. This should fail more gracefully.
